<text id="05-examples" title="nodejs-patterns Worked Example" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="500" depth="medium">
  <summary>One end-to-end worked example for a billing-api service. Inputs, intermediate steps, and final scaffold-spec JSON are shown verbatim.</summary>

  <section title="Inputs">
    <list>
      <item>service_name: billing-api</item>
      <item>resources: [invoice, payment, refund]</item>
      <item>auth_mode: jwt</item>
      <item>node_version: &gt;=20.11.0</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <section title="Intermediate steps">
    <p>Step 2 expands the folder tree for three resources + JWT auth. Step 3 inserts "auth" between "requestLogger" and "routes". Step 4 emits four error classes (AppError, NotFoundError, ValidationError, UnauthorizedError) because auth_mode != "none". Step 5 picks Pino. Step 6 validates and returns.</p>
  </section>

  <example type="good" title="Final scaffold-spec.json">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_id": "billing-api-scaffold",
  "owner": "ruslan@faion.net",
  "service_name": "billing-api",
  "node_version": ">=20.11.0",
  "folder_tree": [
    "src/app.ts",
    "src/server.ts",
    "src/config/env.ts",
    "src/routes/index.ts",
    "src/routes/invoices.ts",
    "src/routes/payments.ts",
    "src/routes/refunds.ts",
    "src/controllers/invoices.controller.ts",
    "src/controllers/payments.controller.ts",
    "src/controllers/refunds.controller.ts",
    "src/services/invoices.service.ts",
    "src/services/payments.service.ts",
    "src/services/refunds.service.ts",
    "src/middleware/auth.ts",
    "src/middleware/errorHandler.ts",
    "src/middleware/requestLogger.ts",
    "src/utils/errors.ts",
    "src/utils/logger.ts",
    "src/utils/asyncHandler.ts"
  ],
  "middleware_order": ["helmet", "cors", "json", "urlencoded", "compression", "requestLogger", "auth", "routes", "errorHandler"],
  "error_classes": [
    {"name": "AppError",          "statusCode": 500, "code": "INTERNAL_ERROR",  "isOperational": true},
    {"name": "NotFoundError",     "statusCode": 404, "code": "NOT_FOUND",       "isOperational": true},
    {"name": "ValidationError",   "statusCode": 400, "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR","isOperational": true},
    {"name": "UnauthorizedError", "statusCode": 401, "code": "UNAUTHORIZED",    "isOperational": true}
  ],
  "logger": {"library": "pino", "request_id_header": "x-request-id"},
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "last_reviewed": "2026-05-22"
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <section title="What downstream consumers do with this">
    <p>A codegen agent reads the spec and writes the actual TS files. A reviewer compares the spec to the current repo and produces a refactor diff. The PR description quotes the spec's middleware_order verbatim — that's the source of truth.</p>
  </section>
</text>
